{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "user_weight_threshold",
    "description": "Threshold sweep varying user node economic weight fraction and initial user fork alignment to find where user nodes transition from structurally irrelevant to causally influential on fork outcomes.\nMOTIVATION: All prior sweeps calibrate user node custody_btc against exchange/institutional proof-of-reserve data, producing a 2197:1 economic weight ratio (user nodes negligible). Real-world data suggests individual self-custody holders control ~65.9% of circulating supply (River Financial / Glassnode, Feb 2026). This sweep tests whether the user null result (bias ratio 1.256 from User-PRIM, Phase 3) is a calibration artifact or a structural finding.\nCONCEPTUAL FRAMING: - Prior sweeps (all existing data): exchange-mediated price discovery \u2014 only liquid,\n  exchange-held Bitcoin participates in price signaling.\n- This sweep: cold-storage activation \u2014 user_custody_fraction represents the fraction\n  of self-custodied BTC whose holders actively signal fork preference. At 0.35,\n  roughly half of the estimated self-custody fraction is engaged; at 0.65, the\n  realistic upper bound of active individual participation.\n\nDESIGN: - 6x5 grid = 30 scenarios - Pool parameters fixed at PRIM uncertainty zone midpoints (contested transition region) - economic_split fixed at 0.60 (inversion zone \u2014 maximum sensitivity to new signals) - user_custody_fraction: 6 levels covering current calibration through realistic range - user_split: 5 levels spanning minority through majority v27 user alignment\nEXPECTED RUNTIME (12 namespaces, large servers): - 30 scenarios / 12 namespaces = ~3 scenarios per namespace - ~3.6 hours per scenario (2016-block retarget) - ~10.8 hours wall-clock\nDECISION RULE FOR PHASE 2: Proceed to lhs_user_weight_prim.yaml if:\n  - Outcomes differ across user_split levels at any user_custody_fraction < 0.40, OR\n  - Non-monotonic patterns observed (not a clean step threshold)\nSkip Phase 2 if:\n  - Null holds uniformly across all user_custody_fraction levels including 0.65\n",
    "spec_file": "tools/sweep/specs/user_weight_threshold.yaml",
    "base_network": "full",
    "n_samples": 30,
    "n_parameters": 16,
